The paper discusses the application of SDN in mobile networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a hybrid design that combines centralized and distributed control, which involves the use of algorithms and optimization techniques (cs.MA) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the security implications of SDN in mobile networks (cs.CR) and the use of information theory in optimizing network performance (cs.IT).
